{
  "stem": "1765.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 201.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so then what?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You didn't have to go somewhere else to be exactly at 8 o'clock in the theater.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Once in a while, we went to the movies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we certainly knew what time we had to be there because everybody was saying, oh, the Deanna Durbin movie will be in this little movie house in Rubtsovsk.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was really-- It was sometimes more relaxed than it is in 'civilization.' You know, it's a different set of priorities.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Time is not one of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You do it when you can, not by a certain hour.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, you had to go to work on time, to school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The war?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The war came to the-- to an end for me-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it's so odd-- when Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my grandmother said, who's going to care-- take care of us now?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who is this Truman?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I knew the war ended because [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] my father was still in-- in Europe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, Siberia is not in Europe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's in Asia, where we were.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't remember a time like D Day here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The thing I remember most now [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] is when Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Of course, we knew that the war ended with-- with Germany through the news, but then Russia, the Soviet Union, declared war on Japan.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And when the war with Japan was over, then war was over for all of us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had prisoners of war in Rubtsovsk, from German prisoners of war and then Japanese prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But my war ended when I left Siberia.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
